Text.SourceString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Look, I made breakfast today. Everything's from scratch. Enjoy!
Text.LocalizedString: Good morning, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Look, I made breakfast today. Everything's from scratch. Enjoy!

Text.SourceString: Tadaa! I made you breakfast, babe. I think it turned out alright. Fingers crossed!
Text.LocalizedString: Tadaa! I made you breakfast, babe. I think it turned out alright. Fingers crossed!

Text.SourceString: Can I start calling myself a farmer, you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I start calling myself a farmer, you think?

Text.SourceString: You just can't beat this air. It's so fresh out here.
Text.LocalizedString: You just can't beat this air. It's so fresh out here.

Text.SourceString: How was your sleep, babe? You look like you got a good night's rest.
Text.LocalizedString: How was your sleep, babe? You look like you got a good night's rest.

Text.SourceString: Got any plans on the agenda today?
Text.LocalizedString: Got any plans on the agenda today?

Text.SourceString: How was your day today? Did anything exciting happen?
Text.LocalizedString: How was your day today? Did anything exciting happen?

Text.SourceString: Our farm is so beautiful. I could just stand here and admire it all day.
Text.LocalizedString: Our farm is so beautiful. I could just stand here and admire it all day.

Text.SourceString: Now that we're married, how about we start some new traditions? Maybe a weekend picnic or game night on Fridays?
Text.LocalizedString: Now that we're married, how about we start some new traditions? Maybe a weekend picnic or game night on Fridays?

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I just want to say...I love you.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I just want to say...I love you.

Text.SourceString: Your kindness is like a force of nature.//The way you care for your friends, for animals...for this farm. You're just as beautiful on the inside as you are on the outside.
Text.LocalizedString: Your kindness is like a force of nature.//The way you care for your friends, for animals...for this farm. You're just as beautiful on the inside as you are on the outside.

Text.SourceString: Wow, babe! Smoking hot!
Text.LocalizedString: Wow, babe! Smoking hot!

Text.SourceString: Come here...give me a kiss.
Text.LocalizedString: Come here...give me a kiss.

Text.SourceString: I feel kind of tired, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Let's turn in early tonight, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: I feel kind of tired, <PlayerName>$Player</>. Let's turn in early tonight, yeah?

Text.SourceString: Hey, babe, I'm feeling a little worn out. Mind if we turn in early tonight?//I could use some extra cuddle time with you.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, babe, I'm feeling a little worn out. Mind if we turn in early tonight?//I could use some extra cuddle time with you.

Text.SourceString: I'm pretty beat, <PlayerName>$Player</>. How about we call it a day and hit the sack early?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm pretty beat, <PlayerName>$Player</>. How about we call it a day and hit the sack early?

Text.SourceString: Babe, I think we both could use some extra rest tonight. Let's tuck in early, yeah?
Text.LocalizedString: Babe, I think we both could use some extra rest tonight. Let's tuck in early, yeah?

Text.SourceString: How about we make today a lazy day, just you and me in bed?
Text.LocalizedString: How about we make today a lazy day, just you and me in bed?

Text.SourceString: Why don't we spend the day huddled up in bed, just enjoying each other's company?
Text.LocalizedString: Why don't we spend the day huddled up in bed, just enjoying each other's company?

Text.SourceString: What if we made today a 'stay in bed' day, all snuggly and warm? I miss you, <PlayerName>$Player</>...
Text.LocalizedString: What if we made today a 'stay in bed' day, all snuggly and warm? I miss you, <PlayerName>$Player</>...

Text.SourceString: Gave the kitchen a good scrub today. Used that potent cleaner from the tavern.//Everything should be sparkling clean now!
Text.LocalizedString: Gave the kitchen a good scrub today. Used that potent cleaner from the tavern.//Everything should be sparkling clean now!

Text.SourceString: Saw a bird smack right into our window this morning...it made a loud thud, got me kind of worried.//<portrait=normal>I'll check on it in a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Saw a bird smack right into our window this morning...it made a loud thud, got me kind of worried.//<portrait=normal>I'll check on it in a bit.

Text.SourceString: Cracked open the windows this morning, freshen things up a bit...//So keep an eye out for bugs, babe. Might get a few uninvited guests today.
Text.LocalizedString: Cracked open the windows this morning, freshen things up a bit...//So keep an eye out for bugs, babe. Might get a few uninvited guests today.

Text.SourceString: I put two layers of blanket for us, in case it gets cold.
Text.LocalizedString: I put two layers of blanket for us, in case it gets cold.

Text.SourceString: Took a little stroll this morning...just around the rice fields and back.
Text.LocalizedString: Took a little stroll this morning...just around the rice fields and back.

Text.SourceString: I'm going to check on Mama later, see how she's doing...
Text.LocalizedString: I'm going to check on Mama later, see how she's doing...

Text.SourceString: Asked <NPCName>Aaliyah</> to keep an extra eye on Mama. This weather doesn't do her hip any favors.
Text.LocalizedString: Asked <NPCName>Aaliyah</> to keep an extra eye on Mama. This weather doesn't do her hip any favors.

Text.SourceString: Can I pick up anything for you from the tavern, babe? Or maybe from Sam's?
Text.LocalizedString: Can I pick up anything for you from the tavern, babe? Or maybe from Sam's?

Text.SourceString: Don't work too hard, okay? I know the Harvest Festival is soon but I want you to take it easy.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't work too hard, okay? I know the Harvest Festival is soon but I want you to take it easy.

Text.SourceString: How 'bout a massage, babe? I saw you putting in some serious work on our farm today...
Text.LocalizedString: How 'bout a massage, babe? I saw you putting in some serious work on our farm today...

Text.SourceString: I might've overwatered the plant in my home office, I saw the new leaves turning yellow. Hmm.
Text.LocalizedString: I might've overwatered the plant in my home office, I saw the new leaves turning yellow. Hmm.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I need to take it out to the farm for a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I need to take it out to the farm for a bit.

Text.SourceString: I put the gloves in my cabinet inside the home office, okay? Be careful opening it though, it's kind of messy.
Text.LocalizedString: I put the gloves in my cabinet inside the home office, okay? Be careful opening it though, it's kind of messy.

Text.SourceString: Can't wait for the Animal Festival tomorrow! Ready to take on that bull ride again. I'm setting a record this year!
Text.LocalizedString: Can't wait for the Animal Festival tomorrow! Ready to take on that bull ride again. I'm setting a record this year!

Text.SourceString: What do you think, babe, should I take a shot at the swimming contest tomorrow? You in?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you think, babe, should I take a shot at the swimming contest tomorrow? You in?

Text.SourceString: Had a close call with burning my fingers off yesterday, playing with those tiny fireworks with <NPCName>Pablo</>...won't be doing that again.//<portrait=happy>Gotta admit it was a bit fun though.
Text.LocalizedString: Had a close call with burning my fingers off yesterday, playing with those tiny fireworks with <NPCName>Pablo</>...won't be doing that again.//<portrait=happy>Gotta admit it was a bit fun though.

Text.SourceString: I like this town. It may not be Pokyo, but it’s home to me.//That’s hard to beat.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this town. It may not be Pokyo, but it’s home to me.//That’s hard to beat.

Text.SourceString: Where else can we get a white-sand beach and a lake, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Where else can we get a white-sand beach and a lake, huh?

Text.SourceString: I like to knock out my errands before lunch. Helps me focus on work later.
Text.LocalizedString: I like to knock out my errands before lunch. Helps me focus on work later.

Text.SourceString: Something about being at the Tavern makes some people share too much, too soon.//<portrait=sad>Hmm…
Text.LocalizedString: Something about being at the Tavern makes some people share too much, too soon.//<portrait=sad>Hmm…

Text.SourceString: It's definitely <NPCName>Frank</>'s mixed punch.
Text.LocalizedString: It's definitely <NPCName>Frank</>'s mixed punch.

Text.SourceString: We do our own grocery shopping and cooking.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s very time consuming, if you ask me.
Text.LocalizedString: We do our own grocery shopping and cooking.//<portrait=annoyed>It’s very time consuming, if you ask me.

Text.SourceString: After working at Fishensips for a while, I think selling drinks is where the money’s at.//<portrait=angry>If it were up to me, the Tavern would cut down on serving food and expand the drink menu.
Text.LocalizedString: After working at Fishensips for a while, I think selling drinks is where the money’s at.//<portrait=angry>If it were up to me, the Tavern would cut down on serving food and expand the drink menu.

Text.SourceString: Besides, serving drinks is much easier than serving food.//Less mess, especially with big parties.
Text.LocalizedString: Besides, serving drinks is much easier than serving food.//Less mess, especially with big parties.

Text.SourceString: You should sign up for the live performance sometime, babe. It doesn't have to be singing...you could do stand-up, or even miming!//We only have <NpcName>Theo</> so far. I think he’s all right. People like his energy.
Text.LocalizedString: You should sign up for the live performance sometime, babe. It doesn't have to be singing...you could do stand-up, or even miming!//We only have <NpcName>Theo</> so far. I think he’s all right. People like his energy.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Theo</> gets some quick money, and we get to advertise live music at the Tavern.//<portrait=normal>People are drawn to live music for some reason.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Theo</> gets some quick money, and we get to advertise live music at the Tavern.//<portrait=normal>People are drawn to live music for some reason.

Text.SourceString: Hey, how's it going, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, how's it going, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Frank</> is a good cook. But not much variety, you know?//<portrait=normal>He also has this tendency to substitute ingredients.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Frank</> is a good cook. But not much variety, you know?//<portrait=normal>He also has this tendency to substitute ingredients.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes you don’t really know what you’re getting yourself into.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes you don’t really know what you’re getting yourself into.

Text.SourceString: Finding the right balance between working and taking time for yourself is important.//It helps you refocus on your goals.
Text.LocalizedString: Finding the right balance between working and taking time for yourself is important.//It helps you refocus on your goals.

Text.SourceString: Having three siblings taught me there’s no such thing as personal space.
Text.LocalizedString: Having three siblings taught me there’s no such thing as personal space.

Text.SourceString: Gah. I miss <NpcName>Eddy</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Gah. I miss <NpcName>Eddy</>.

Text.SourceString: When I was growing up, Mama and Dad assigned each of us a roommate.//<portrait=happy>I got <NPCName>Frank</>, and our sis was stuck with baby bro <NPCName>Eddy</>.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was growing up, Mama and Dad assigned each of us a roommate.//<portrait=happy>I got <NPCName>Frank</>, and our sis was stuck with baby bro <NPCName>Eddy</>.

Text.SourceString: I hope it won’t rain tomorrow. I need to visit the vineyard to pick up some wine…//<portrait=normal>The Tavern is dangerously low.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it won’t rain tomorrow. I need to visit the vineyard to pick up some wine…//<portrait=normal>The Tavern is dangerously low.

Text.SourceString: Please, don't order the 'mixed punch' - it's basically <NPCName>Frank</>'s failed experiment.//Save your stomach the trouble.
Text.LocalizedString: Please, don't order the 'mixed punch' - it's basically <NPCName>Frank</>'s failed experiment.//Save your stomach the trouble.

Text.SourceString: I grew up eating <NpcName>Frank’s</> experimental food, probably why I'm picky about food now.
Text.LocalizedString: I grew up eating <NpcName>Frank’s</> experimental food, probably why I'm picky about food now.

Text.SourceString: The Tavern could charge a premium for drinks and meals, don’t you think? We use only the best ingredients.
Text.LocalizedString: The Tavern could charge a premium for drinks and meals, don’t you think? We use only the best ingredients.

Text.SourceString: I don't think a 20% price hike would drive people away. But we’re too afraid to risk it, I guess.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't think a 20% price hike would drive people away. But we’re too afraid to risk it, I guess.

Text.SourceString: One thing I don’t miss about Pokyo, though, is the constant blaring of car horns.
Text.LocalizedString: One thing I don’t miss about Pokyo, though, is the constant blaring of car horns.

Text.SourceString: I lost a lot of sleep because of that, which inevitably affected my mood.
Text.LocalizedString: I lost a lot of sleep because of that, which inevitably affected my mood.

Text.SourceString: Honestly, at this point, I’m just counting down the days until Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: Honestly, at this point, I’m just counting down the days until Summer.

Text.SourceString: If Mama can cook seasonal food, why can’t <NPCName>Frank</>? And why can’t we serve it at the Tavern?//<portrait=normal>Now’s the perfect time for a seasonal menu.
Text.LocalizedString: If Mama can cook seasonal food, why can’t <NPCName>Frank</>? And why can’t we serve it at the Tavern?//<portrait=normal>Now’s the perfect time for a seasonal menu.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> and I are getting ready for the Cherry Blossom Festival.//Mama and Dad used to help make the hot pot, but we took over, even before Dad passed away.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> and I are getting ready for the Cherry Blossom Festival.//Mama and Dad used to help make the hot pot, but we took over, even before Dad passed away.

Text.SourceString: Back in Pokyo, the trees never held this kind of charm in Spring. I'm so grateful that I decided to move back after graduation.
Text.LocalizedString: Back in Pokyo, the trees never held this kind of charm in Spring. I'm so grateful that I decided to move back after graduation.

Text.SourceString: That choice led me straight to you - I wouldn't rewrite history even if I could.
Text.LocalizedString: That choice led me straight to you - I wouldn't rewrite history even if I could.

Text.SourceString: I’m gathering all the ingredients for the hot pot.//<portrait=happy>Well, other than the ones the townsfolk are bringing, of course.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m gathering all the ingredients for the hot pot.//<portrait=happy>Well, other than the ones the townsfolk are bringing, of course.

Text.SourceString: Finally, it’s Summer!//What are we planting this Summer, baby?
Text.LocalizedString: Finally, it’s Summer!//What are we planting this Summer, baby?

Text.SourceString: As the heat kicks in, I'm thinking of swapping beach walks with Mama for some Hillside strolls… Too much beach can be a bit much for her.
Text.LocalizedString: As the heat kicks in, I'm thinking of swapping beach walks with Mama for some Hillside strolls… Too much beach can be a bit much for her.

Text.SourceString: The AC broke the other day. Thank goodness for <NPCName>Pablo</>.//Moldy wiring of all things. Just glad it wasn't a rat issue.
Text.LocalizedString: The AC broke the other day. Thank goodness for <NPCName>Pablo</>.//Moldy wiring of all things. Just glad it wasn't a rat issue.

Text.SourceString: Been toying with the idea of opening a festival booth, like for the annual beach cleanup. Sounds cool, right?//Selling cold drinks, homemade sweets… People get out of the water, they're gonna be hungry,//But <NPCName>Frank</> won’t even give it a chance. Not enough staff.
Text.LocalizedString: Been toying with the idea of opening a festival booth, like for the annual beach cleanup. Sounds cool, right?//Selling cold drinks, homemade sweets… People get out of the water, they're gonna be hungry,//But <NPCName>Frank</> won’t even give it a chance. Not enough staff.

Text.SourceString: Got to make sure Mama wears her hat. Summer heat and no hat? Bad combo.//I’m worried she might get light-headed at the lake, and…//I don’t even wanna think about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Got to make sure Mama wears her hat. Summer heat and no hat? Bad combo.//I’m worried she might get light-headed at the lake, and…//I don’t even wanna think about it.

Text.SourceString: Summer tides can get pretty intense, but so far, the Tavern's safe.//Thank goodness. That sounds expensive to fix.
Text.LocalizedString: Summer tides can get pretty intense, but so far, the Tavern's safe.//Thank goodness. That sounds expensive to fix.

Text.SourceString: Ever heard of the old folk story about daisy patches in Summer? Says they mark where a pure and innocent child was laid to rest.
Text.LocalizedString: Ever heard of the old folk story about daisy patches in Summer? Says they mark where a pure and innocent child was laid to rest.

Text.SourceString: There's also another version that says fairies sleep there.//Personally, I'm team fairy.
Text.LocalizedString: There's also another version that says fairies sleep there.//Personally, I'm team fairy.

Text.SourceString: Such a bummer that Summer is over. But I guess it means I can focus more on the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: Such a bummer that Summer is over. But I guess it means I can focus more on the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: The beach is still pretty fun in Fall, but not as much as it is in Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: The beach is still pretty fun in Fall, but not as much as it is in Summer.

Text.SourceString: Gotta say, babe, Fall's the prime time for some good roasted mushrooms. Perfect season for finding them too!//They pop up everywhere in the forest.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta say, babe, Fall's the prime time for some good roasted mushrooms. Perfect season for finding them too!//They pop up everywhere in the forest.

Text.SourceString: Who eats mushrooms raw, seriously? Gross.//<portrait=happy>Now, give me a nicely roasted one any day.
Text.LocalizedString: Who eats mushrooms raw, seriously? Gross.//<portrait=happy>Now, give me a nicely roasted one any day.

Text.SourceString: I managed to find tons of mushrooms the other day! Now I just need to roast them all.//Not a big fan of cleaning them, though. It’s a lot of work.//The dirt just doesn’t seem to come off.
Text.LocalizedString: I managed to find tons of mushrooms the other day! Now I just need to roast them all.//Not a big fan of cleaning them, though. It’s a lot of work.//The dirt just doesn’t seem to come off.

Text.SourceString: Got your party hat ready for New Year's Eve Festival, babe? I'm ready to go.//<portrait=happy>Yeah, yeah, I know it's only the first week of Winter, but early bird gets the worm.
Text.LocalizedString: Got your party hat ready for New Year's Eve Festival, babe? I'm ready to go.//<portrait=happy>Yeah, yeah, I know it's only the first week of Winter, but early bird gets the worm.

Text.SourceString: Can't wait for the New Year’s Eve Festival.//The Duckorns always bring in food from the fancy Pokyo restaurants.//Remember the garlic ice cream they served a few years back? Weirdly delicious.
Text.LocalizedString: Can't wait for the New Year’s Eve Festival.//The Duckorns always bring in food from the fancy Pokyo restaurants.//Remember the garlic ice cream they served a few years back? Weirdly delicious.

Text.SourceString: Can't say I'm a huge fan of the cold, but then, who really is?//<portrait=surprised>Wait… Are you, <PlayerName>$Player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Can't say I'm a huge fan of the cold, but then, who really is?//<portrait=surprised>Wait… Are you, <PlayerName>$Player</>?

Text.SourceString: If it were warmer, I think I’d spend more time outside, but as it is?//<portrait=normal>I think I’ll just do the paperwork for the Tavern.//Somebody’s gotta do the accounting, and it isn’t gonna be my big bro.
Text.LocalizedString: If it were warmer, I think I’d spend more time outside, but as it is?//<portrait=normal>I think I’ll just do the paperwork for the Tavern.//Somebody’s gotta do the accounting, and it isn’t gonna be my big bro.

Text.SourceString: *humming*
Text.LocalizedString: *humming*

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> will be grilling all day tomorrow, so we should probably arrive a bit early to get things ready.//What do you think? Would that work for you?
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> will be grilling all day tomorrow, so we should probably arrive a bit early to get things ready.//What do you think? Would that work for you?

Text.SourceString: They should at least consider having another potluck this Summer.
Text.LocalizedString: They should at least consider having another potluck this Summer.

Text.SourceString: What if we had a potluck in Fall and Winter too?//When everyone brings their favorite dish for everyone to enjoy, it feels like one big family gathering.
Text.LocalizedString: What if we had a potluck in Fall and Winter too?//When everyone brings their favorite dish for everyone to enjoy, it feels like one big family gathering.

Text.SourceString: Get ready, babe, tomorrow is the first day of Summer. We’re about to crank up the heat.
Text.LocalizedString: Get ready, babe, tomorrow is the first day of Summer. We’re about to crank up the heat.

Text.SourceString: I know it’s only Spring, but I'm already daydreaming about spending my Summer days at the beach with you.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it’s only Spring, but I'm already daydreaming about spending my Summer days at the beach with you.

Text.SourceString: Have you heard that merfolk supposedly come out in the warmer weather? I know it sounds odd and is impossible to prove, but it's kind of fun to think about.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you heard that merfolk supposedly come out in the warmer weather? I know it sounds odd and is impossible to prove, but it's kind of fun to think about.

Text.SourceString: I’m taking a bit of a break today, just trying to spend time outdoors.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m taking a bit of a break today, just trying to spend time outdoors.

Text.SourceString: It’s Summer, after all. Right?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s Summer, after all. Right?

Text.SourceString: Hmm… It feels incredibly humid today!//<portrait=annoyed>I hate the sticky feeling in Summer.//<portrait=concerned>The heat is nice sometimes, but when it’s this hot, just being outside can be tiring. Even if I’m doing nothing.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… It feels incredibly humid today!//<portrait=annoyed>I hate the sticky feeling in Summer.//<portrait=concerned>The heat is nice sometimes, but when it’s this hot, just being outside can be tiring. Even if I’m doing nothing.

Text.SourceString: Sorry if I’m complaining too much.//<portrait=sad>I guess it’s just one of those days.
Text.LocalizedString: Sorry if I’m complaining too much.//<portrait=sad>I guess it’s just one of those days.

Text.SourceString: I picked up some coconuts from the beach the other day. They can be a quick hydration solution…//<portrait=surprised>Bah!//<portrait=blushing>That was a mouthful to say.
Text.LocalizedString: I picked up some coconuts from the beach the other day. They can be a quick hydration solution…//<portrait=surprised>Bah!//<portrait=blushing>That was a mouthful to say.

Text.SourceString: The wind is getting colder. I think Fall is finally here.
Text.LocalizedString: The wind is getting colder. I think Fall is finally here.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> usually needs an extra hand in the Fall, so I’m thinking of picking up some extra shifts on Sundays.//That way, I can also keep an eye on Mama.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> usually needs an extra hand in the Fall, so I’m thinking of picking up some extra shifts on Sundays.//That way, I can also keep an eye on Mama.

Text.SourceString: Taking a break from farming, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Taking a break from farming, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: I’ve been baking a lot more lately, but nothing’s turned out good… Bummer!
Text.LocalizedString: I’ve been baking a lot more lately, but nothing’s turned out good… Bummer!

Text.SourceString: I usually don't crave sweets, but I reckon the cold weather's making me hungrier than usual.
Text.LocalizedString: I usually don't crave sweets, but I reckon the cold weather's making me hungrier than usual.

Text.SourceString: It’s truffle season. I’m keeping an eye out in case I spot one in the wild.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s truffle season. I’m keeping an eye out in case I spot one in the wild.

Text.SourceString: They're pretty rare finds though.
Text.LocalizedString: They're pretty rare finds though.

Text.SourceString: When I was a kid, Mama and I would spend my birthday hunting for truffles and Winter veggies in the forest.//Then, she'd cook them up as a side dish for ramen.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was a kid, Mama and I would spend my birthday hunting for truffles and Winter veggies in the forest.//Then, she'd cook them up as a side dish for ramen.

Text.SourceString: <NPCName>Frank</> decided we needed a new heater for the Tavern and splurged on it.
Text.LocalizedString: <NPCName>Frank</> decided we needed a new heater for the Tavern and splurged on it.

Text.SourceString: The old one was working just fine, but <NPCName>Frank</> insisted we get a new one, just in case.
Text.LocalizedString: The old one was working just fine, but <NPCName>Frank</> insisted we get a new one, just in case.

Text.SourceString: I'm proud of myself, haven't grumbled about the cold once this Winter!
Text.LocalizedString: I'm proud of myself, haven't grumbled about the cold once this Winter!

Text.SourceString: The weather is putting people in a good mood.
Text.LocalizedString: The weather is putting people in a good mood.

Text.SourceString: You must not have a lot of watering to do today, eh?
Text.LocalizedString: You must not have a lot of watering to do today, eh?

Text.SourceString: I hope there isn’t a leak in our house.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope there isn’t a leak in our house.

Text.SourceString: I’m going to check on the roof when the rain settles down.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m going to check on the roof when the rain settles down.

Text.SourceString: Something warm sounds good right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Something warm sounds good right now.

Text.SourceString: Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?

Text.SourceString: The Tavern tends to turn into a mud pit when it rains. People just forget to wipe their shoes.
Text.LocalizedString: The Tavern tends to turn into a mud pit when it rains. People just forget to wipe their shoes.

Text.SourceString: Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it actually darker than usual outside, or am I losing my mind?

Text.SourceString: The tavern gets extra muddy when it rains.//<portrait=annoyed>People just don’t bother wiping their feet.
Text.LocalizedString: The tavern gets extra muddy when it rains.//<portrait=annoyed>People just don’t bother wiping their feet.

Text.SourceString: Oh, um…be safe out there, babe.//The storm is really bad today.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, um…be safe out there, babe.//The storm is really bad today.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know if it’s safe to walk around in this weather.//<portrait=sad>What am I thinking?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know if it’s safe to walk around in this weather.//<portrait=sad>What am I thinking?

Text.SourceString: Your cheeks are getting red. You need to warm up, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Your cheeks are getting red. You need to warm up, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: When I was in elementary school, our sister would boil potatoes in the morning to put in our coat pockets.
Text.LocalizedString: When I was in elementary school, our sister would boil potatoes in the morning to put in our coat pockets.

Text.SourceString: The potatoes were to keep our hands warm.//Then we would eat them when we got to school.
Text.LocalizedString: The potatoes were to keep our hands warm.//Then we would eat them when we got to school.

Text.SourceString: I've been trying to convince Mama to see <NPCName>Yuri</> for her hip pain, but she's brushing it off as just a part of growing old.
Text.LocalizedString: I've been trying to convince Mama to see <NPCName>Yuri</> for her hip pain, but she's brushing it off as just a part of growing old.

Text.SourceString: Even if it’s just normal joint pain, why not get a professional opinion, right?
Text.LocalizedString: Even if it’s just normal joint pain, why not get a professional opinion, right?

Text.SourceString: I bumped my head trying to clean the cabinet this morning.
Text.LocalizedString: I bumped my head trying to clean the cabinet this morning.

Text.SourceString: It still hurts.
Text.LocalizedString: It still hurts.

Text.SourceString: I've made it a habit to check the weather every morning before heading out.//You know, just in case there's a chance of rain or something.
Text.LocalizedString: I've made it a habit to check the weather every morning before heading out.//You know, just in case there's a chance of rain or something.

Text.SourceString: I’ll just have a small breakfast here before my doctor’s appointment at noon.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll just have a small breakfast here before my doctor’s appointment at noon.

Text.SourceString: All good, just a routine checkup, babe.
Text.LocalizedString: All good, just a routine checkup, babe.

Text.SourceString: Caught one of my brother’s mischievous cats trying to sneak in here, can you believe it?
Text.LocalizedString: Caught one of my brother’s mischievous cats trying to sneak in here, can you believe it?

Text.SourceString: I’ll check on the cats later before I go to work.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll check on the cats later before I go to work.

Text.SourceString: *mumbling* Oil, two loaves of bread…
Text.LocalizedString: *mumbling* Oil, two loaves of bread…

Text.SourceString: No matter how often you sweep the Tavern’s balcony, it’s impossible to keep it clean this time of year.//Leaves, leaves, everywhere.
Text.LocalizedString: No matter how often you sweep the Tavern’s balcony, it’s impossible to keep it clean this time of year.//Leaves, leaves, everywhere.

Text.SourceString: Just looking down this cliff gives me a headache...//Can't do it. Nope.
Text.LocalizedString: Just looking down this cliff gives me a headache...//Can't do it. Nope.

Text.SourceString: Maybe I'll let my hair grow out a bit. What do you say, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Do you like men with long hair?
Text.LocalizedString: Maybe I'll let my hair grow out a bit. What do you say, <PlayerName>$Player</>? Do you like men with long hair?

Text.SourceString: I might stay here a little longer to cool off.
Text.LocalizedString: I might stay here a little longer to cool off.

Text.SourceString: It’s so hot outside.//I’m glad <NpcName>Sam</> has his air conditioner on full blast.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so hot outside.//I’m glad <NpcName>Sam</> has his air conditioner on full blast.

Text.SourceString: Oh, bees! Why is it so cold in here?!//<portrait=surprised>With the snow and all, you would think <NpcName>Sam</> would turn down the coolers a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, bees! Why is it so cold in here?!//<portrait=surprised>With the snow and all, you would think <NpcName>Sam</> would turn down the coolers a bit.

Text.SourceString: *shivers* I’ve got to get my shopping done fast. It’s too cold in here.//I can’t think.
Text.LocalizedString: *shivers* I’ve got to get my shopping done fast. It’s too cold in here.//I can’t think.

Text.SourceString: With all these coconuts around the island, it got me thinking. Maybe we could start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips?//Hydrating, low-cost...but, the thing is that the Beach Shack already sells those.
Text.LocalizedString: With all these coconuts around the island, it got me thinking. Maybe we could start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips?//Hydrating, low-cost...but, the thing is that the Beach Shack already sells those.

Text.SourceString: I'm kinda on the fence. Maybe I should run it by <NPCName>Aaliyah</>?
Text.LocalizedString: I'm kinda on the fence. Maybe I should run it by <NPCName>Aaliyah</>?

Text.SourceString: With all these coconuts around the island, it got me thinking. Maybe we could start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips? Hydrating, low-cost...
Text.LocalizedString: With all these coconuts around the island, it got me thinking. Maybe we could start selling coconut drinks at Fishensips? Hydrating, low-cost...

Text.SourceString: But then again, the Beach Shack is already doing that... I'm kinda on the fence. Maybe I should run it by <NPCName>Aaliyah</>?
Text.LocalizedString: But then again, the Beach Shack is already doing that... I'm kinda on the fence. Maybe I should run it by <NPCName>Aaliyah</>?

Text.SourceString: I know it's just the beginning of Winter, but let me tell you something, babe. The second Summer rolls around, we're going to the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: I know it's just the beginning of Winter, but let me tell you something, babe. The second Summer rolls around, we're going to the beach.

Text.SourceString: We'll camp there and enjoy every minute of the salty Summer breeze.
Text.LocalizedString: We'll camp there and enjoy every minute of the salty Summer breeze.

Text.SourceString: It's a little sad seeing the cats now. They remind me so much of Dad.
Text.LocalizedString: It's a little sad seeing the cats now. They remind me so much of Dad.

Text.SourceString: They've been around since he was here...don't even know how old they are.
Text.LocalizedString: They've been around since he was here...don't even know how old they are.

Text.SourceString: Remember me telling you about my university days? I lived next to this temple, and whenever Mama came to visit, we'd go there and pray.//<portrait=happy>Mama would make sure we burned enough incense for our ancestors.
Text.LocalizedString: Remember me telling you about my university days? I lived next to this temple, and whenever Mama came to visit, we'd go there and pray.//<portrait=happy>Mama would make sure we burned enough incense for our ancestors.

Text.SourceString: I remember smelling like ash for the rest of the day.//<portrait=normal>Here, we only pray at the house or at Dad’s grave.
Text.LocalizedString: I remember smelling like ash for the rest of the day.//<portrait=normal>Here, we only pray at the house or at Dad’s grave.

Text.SourceString: Usually, when I get headaches like this, it’s because I need a new prescription for my glasses.
Text.LocalizedString: Usually, when I get headaches like this, it’s because I need a new prescription for my glasses.

Text.SourceString: Ugh… This can’t be good.
Text.LocalizedString: Ugh… This can’t be good.

Text.SourceString: Do I have cat hair on me?
Text.LocalizedString: Do I have cat hair on me?

Text.SourceString: I played with <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> earlier, and there was a lot of hair on my shirt.//I think I got most of it off.
Text.LocalizedString: I played with <NPCName>Peanut</> and <NPCName>Butter</> earlier, and there was a lot of hair on my shirt.//I think I got most of it off.

Text.SourceString: I’m really looking forward to all the fun things we have planned for this Spring.//Everything’s gonna start to bloom soon!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m really looking forward to all the fun things we have planned for this Spring.//Everything’s gonna start to bloom soon!

Text.SourceString: One of the only good things about Summer is the fact that you can wear colorful shirts, but even that gets old after a while.
Text.LocalizedString: One of the only good things about Summer is the fact that you can wear colorful shirts, but even that gets old after a while.

Text.SourceString: I hope we don’t start getting half-naked customers, being near the beach and all.//<portrait=annoyed>The only place where it’s socially acceptable to wear a bathing suit and flip-flops all day is the beach, never the Tavern.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope we don’t start getting half-naked customers, being near the beach and all.//<portrait=annoyed>The only place where it’s socially acceptable to wear a bathing suit and flip-flops all day is the beach, never the Tavern.

Text.SourceString: I’m so glad Spring is here! The weather is finally starting to warm up.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m so glad Spring is here! The weather is finally starting to warm up.

Text.SourceString: I’m looking forward to going on long walks with you and enjoying the beautiful Fall scenery.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m looking forward to going on long walks with you and enjoying the beautiful Fall scenery.

Text.SourceString: I’m really enjoying the slower pace of life in Fall. It’s a nice change from the busy Summer.//<portrait=happy>The beach is peaceful again. Ha ha!
Text.LocalizedString: I’m really enjoying the slower pace of life in Fall. It’s a nice change from the busy Summer.//<portrait=happy>The beach is peaceful again. Ha ha!
